Description: Several fragments of a three element plait made of dark brown human hair and undyed flax. One element is flax and the other two are hair. The flax element is largely missing. The hair elements consist of 2 'z'-spun yarns, 'z'-plied. The flax element consists of 4 'z'-plied yarns.
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p. 65)
Condition: Fair. The flax element is largely missing.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: 93.1.189B (excavation object cat. no.)
